  "full_text": "An update for llvm-toolset:rhel8 is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 10.\n\nLLVM Toolset provides the LLVM compiler infrastructure framework, the Clang compiler for the C and C++ languages, the LLDB debugger, and related tools for code analysis.Bug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s): Rebase LLVM Toolset to LLVM 20 [rhel-8] (JIRA:RHEL-81007)  Drop ARM and Mips targets [rhel-8] (JIRA:RHEL-86091)  clang-devel should depend on llvm-devel [rhel-8] [rhel-next stream] (JIRA:RHEL-87252)  Remove llvm19 compat package from the buildroot [rhel-8] (JIRA:RHEL-81016)  size of debuginfo of LLVM compat libs is too big and causes abidiff to segfault [rhel-8.10.z] (JIRA:RHEL-89980)  Update LLVM Toolset to 20.1.8 [rhel-8] (JIRA:RHEL-81022)  Post-20.1.8 llvm backports [rhel-8] (JIRA:RHEL-106427)"
